on is from the tm package, and is used to create a corpus object from a source text (in this case, VectorSource(tesla$tweet)). The VectorSource() function is used to create a source vector from the tweet column of the tesla data frame, which contains the text of the tweets.\n\nThe corpus[[1]][1] line extracts the first word of the first document in the corpus. ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Extract corpus\ncorpus = Corpus(VectorSource(tesla$tweet))\ncorpus[[1]][1]","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-04-14T00:36:58.275967Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-04-14T00:36:58.277108Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-04-14T00:36:58.293679Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":24,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"<strong>$content</strong> = 'If you are curious about the P85D, you can schedule a test drive here: http://ts.la/dE¬†'","text/markdown":"**$content** = 'If you are curious about the P85D, you can schedule a test drive here: http://ts.la/dE¬†'","text/latex":"\\textbf{\\$content} = 'If you are curious about the P85D, you can schedule a test drive here: http://ts.la/dE¬†'","text/plain":"$content\n[1] \"If you are curious about the P85D, you can schedule a test drive here: http://ts.la/dE¬†\"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Convert to lower case\nThis R code is using the tm_map() function from the tm package to transform the text in a corpus to lowercase.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Convert to lower case\ncorpus = tm_map(corpus, FUN = content_transformer(tolower))\ncorpus[[1]][1]","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-04-14T00:36:58.296704Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-04-14T00:36:58.297754Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-04-14T00:36:58.327136Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":25,"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"Warning message in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(corpus, FUN = content_transformer(tolower)):\n‚Äútransformation drops documents‚Äù\n","output_type":"stream"},{